ady for the user. I installed `recharts`, `date-fns`, and `react-markdown`, with `@tailwindcss/typography` already included. The app includes a Carbon Dashboard, Activity Logging, and an AI Coach. I plan to present these features now to the user.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have implemented the **EcoTrack AI** platform using Next.js, React, and Tailwind CSS. The application is now live and fully functional in your preview window! \n\n### Features Implemented:\n- **Carbon Dashboard**: Clean, responsive layout with an overview of total CO\342\202\202 logged and Eco Points earned.\n- **Activity Form**: Easily log transportation, dietary choices, and energy usage with automatic calculations using standard emission factors.\n- **Data Visualization**: Integrated `recharts` for interactive weekly tracking of your carbon footprint.\n- **AI Sustainability Coach**: A fully functional AI chat assistant using the Gemini API to provide actionable, encouraging advice on reducing emissions.\n- **Gamified Challenges**: Built-in eco challenges (like \"Meat-Free Monday\" or \"No Plastic Day\") that users can check off to earn points.\n\n### How to Submit to GitHub from AI Studio\n\nSince you are building this directly in Google AI Studio, you don\'t need to manually bundle or zip files in a terminal. You can easily export this project directly:\n\n1. Look in the top right corner of your AI Studio interface.\n2. Click the **Settings/Menu icon** (often a gear or three dots).\n3. Select **\"Export to GitHub\"** (or **\"Download as ZIP\"**).\n   - *If using Export to GitHub*: Follow the prompts to connect your GitHub account and it will automatically create a public repository and push the code for you in a single branch.\n   - *If using Download as ZIP*: Extract the folder on your local machine, open your terminal in that folder, and run your standard git commands:\n     ```bash\n     git init\n     git add .\n     git commit -m \"Initial commit of EcoTrack AI\"\n     git branch -M main\n     git remote add origin https://github.com/<YOUR_GITHUB_USERNAME>/ecotrack-ai.git\n     git push -u origin main\n     ```\n4. Copy the GitHub URL and submit it to the Hack2Skill portal!\n\nLet me know if you want to tweak any of the UI colors, 